snippet.textDisplay:
As far as I can tell, because I didn't even know who geoff keighley was, he was a journalist on gametrailers and once worked at g4tv. Big fucking deal. No one cares. He is literally a nobody at this point; You don't "need" journalists when the content is literally broadcasted live and straight forward. That's like saying "We need journalists to tell us what this person, who is clearly speaking to us, is saying...because we can't decipher their words properly or coherently enough". Besides, ONE journalist 'not' going isn't changing shit.
Sony dipped from E3 as a way to spike popularity 'against' Microsoft (for some stupid reason) and to counter the performance-to-price by undercutting them without any sort of public presentation to revolve around. That's it. Sony knows they could still push their information out there, and it won't get 'as much' publicity at this event, but it would certainly still give them 'leverage' from withdrawing, so their fanbase will simply 'look out' for the information elsewhere.
Otherwise, Nintendo is not at e3 legitimately due to other reasons (location verses cost), but they still do a 'direct'.
